'''''Star Wars'' 11''' is the eleventh issue of the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']]. It was written by [[Archie Goodwin]], illustrated by [[Carmine Infantino]] and [[Terry Austin]], and first published by [[Marvel Comics]] on [[February 7]], [[1978]]. It features the story "'''Star Search!'''," in which [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] continue their search for [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] in the [[Drexel system/Legends|Drexel system]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Han and Chewie are captured by space pirates while Luke takes on a monstrous Sea-Dragon!''

==Plot summary==
Han Solo and Chewbacca leave [[Aduba-3/Legends|Aduba-3]] in the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], only to be captured once again by [[Crimson Jack/Legends|Crimson Jack]] and his gang of pirates. [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] had also been captured by the pirate while on her way to the [[Drexel system/Legends|Drexel system]] to find out what happened to Luke Skywalker, and Jack intended to hold the princess for ransom. Han and Leia secretly devise a ruse to trick the pirates into taking them to the Drexel system by claiming that the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] have stockpiled a treasure there. While suspicious of Solo's plan, Jack's greed gets the better of him, and he decides to trust the Rebels for the time being.

Meanwhile, on [[Drexel/Legends|Drexel]], Luke, [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]], and [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] are stranded on their wrecked [[Starship/Legends|spacecraft]] floating in the huge [[Ocean/Legends|ocean]] that covers the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] and are attacked by a giant sea-dragon.

==Development==
This is the first issue produced by the creative team of [[Archie Goodwin]] and [[Carmine Infantino]].

